, \"text\": \"Greek Basket League championship\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_Basket_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_Basket_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 0.9359470202033183, \"rank\": 0.06843654439070572, \"text\": \"MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3164728890693383e-44, \"text\": \"Chinese Basketball Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shanghai_Sharks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shanghai Sharks\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shanghai_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shanghai_Sharks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, he transitioned to 3x3 basketball, quickly becoming the most recognizable face of Team USA's squad.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999982082954, \"rank\": 1.7907489213467443e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3x3 basketball, a variant of the traditional 5-on-5 game, has its roots in street basketball from the USA's urban areas in the late 1980s.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1440, \"end\": 1443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9875457937907858, \"rank\": 0.005757112795376762, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The game is played on a half court with three players per team and one substitute.\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It features a 12-second shot clock, a 10-minute game duration, and a first-to-21 points rule.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This fast-paced, physical format demands versatility from its players as they are required to play multiple roles.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fredette and his teammates, Canyon Barry, Kareem Maddox, and Dylan Travis, have honed their chemistry over two years on the FIBA 3x3 World Tour.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Barry\", \"score\": 0.9976658326479017, \"rank\": 0.0021495107107724234, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Barry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Barry\"}, {\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dylan\", \"score\": 0.9999999990941433, \"rank\": 9.057619890596608e-10, \"text\": \"Dylan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dylan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dylan\"}, {\"begin\": 1837, \"end\": 1843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\", \"score\": 0.9999695809808223, \"rank\": 3.041994433719437e-05, \"text\": \"Travis\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their impressive performances, including a gold medal at the Pan-American Games and a top-three ranking on the circuit, earned them a spot in the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1976, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9988999804544801, \"rank\": 0.0011012309209320152, \"text\": \"Pan-American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cColorado isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t really known as a basketball state, so it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cool to represent that aspect of Colorado that flies under the radar,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Barry said in aninterview.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Avalanche\", \"score\": 0.9426324907260231, \"rank\": 0.0296455622712847, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q4498974\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Avalanche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Avalanche\"}, {\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Barry\", \"score\": 0.9976658326479017, \"rank\": 0.0021495107107724234, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Barry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Barry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd with these local ties, Paris is an unbelievable chance to show the world, and especially the U.S., what 3x3 is about.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Fredette's transition to 3x3 allowed him to balance his professional aspirations with family life in Littleton, Colorado.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999878241398, \"rank\": 1.2175737955573283e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fredette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\"}, {\"begin\": 2485, \"end\": 2493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Avalanche\", \"score\": 0.9426324907260231, \"rank\": 0.0296455622712847, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q4498974\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Avalanche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Avalanche\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Training at the Elite Performance Center, he has adapted to the physical demands and fast pace of the game.\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fredette's teammates have also contributed significantly.\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2604, \"end\": 2612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fredette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmer_Fredette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barry, known for his downhill driving and unique underhand free throw style, and Maddox, with his defensive prowess, round out a team ready to challenge the best in the world, including top-ranked Serbia and defending Olympic champion Latvia.\", \"from\"